expandableSections.content:
Express error handlers have FOUR parameters:

```javascript
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  console.error(err.stack);
  res.status(err.status || 500).json({
    error: err.message || 'Internal Server Error'
  });
});
```

When any middleware/route calls `next(error)` or throws, Express skips to the nearest 4-argument middleware. This centralizes error handling.

